article.headline: Boston College falls in ACC tourney
article.linkText: No. 25 Boston College falls in ACC first round
article.story:
GREENSBORO, North Carolina (Ticker) -- Sharnee Zoll and Tiffany 
Sardin prevented Boston College from having a lengthy stay in
the Atlantic Coast Conference tournament. 

Zoll scored 18 points and Sardin added 17 and 10 rebounds to 
help Virginia edge the Eagles (No. 25 ESPN/USA Today; Unranked AP), 57-54, in an 
opening-round game.

The eighth-seeded Cavaliers (18-10) advance to play top seed
North Carolina in Friday's quarterfinals.

Virginia shot just 39 percent from the floor (24-of-62) but
limited Boston College to 36 percent (23-of-64).

Brooke Queenan scored 11 points to pace the ninth-seeded Eagles
(19-11) but committed eight of their 19 turnovers.  She also
shot just 5-of-16.

Boston College held a 10-point lead eight minutes into the game
but settled for a 29-29 tie at the break.

Virginia led by as many as nine points early in the second half
before BC pulled into a 46-46 tie on a jumper by Aja Parham with
6:13 to play.  The Cavaliers took the lead for good, 51-48, on
a 3-pointer by Zoll with 4:14 left.
